Every time someone says FFF is fucked up and needs professional help, all non-professionals jump to his aid.

The people who don't like all of FFF's dls usually just  leave those ones alone, but a few take the time to post.  Good for them.

To look at FFF's stuff is to see a man who does not judge his audience, he has a wonderful sense of humor, and his moral censorship would not stop the variously hot/lame/disgusting/offensive material from being produced.

Therefore, the discussion threads are education forums, and I thank FFF for his continued patience and unselfish sharing of his time and material.

Too many Americans believe the lie that to view something is to endorse it.  The truth is, anyone's presence here endorses free file sharing.  In a very small way, we are all keeping the Internet (mostly) free for its users, and more importantly, we are protecting the rights of the disenfranchised, not trampling those rights.

As a final example, several pedophiles have been tracked down around the world because of file sharing, and the Internet is a policeman's dream, where showing their identity is not a matter of the investigative process.


In other words, Internet material as a whole is ALL contributive to our democratic views of justice and fairness.  

Selective morality is the most subtle and vicious form of evil.

Thus endeth the lesson.
